@sarroth  
Really, they wouldn't be able to attach Mask of Riddles to a creature with Protection from Black anyway, since it can't be targeted by anything Black. The only time it really matters that a Protection creature can't be equipped by something of its Protection color is that you can't use a [Magnetic Theft](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magnetic Theft) or similar card to attach a [Behemoth Sledge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Behemoth Sledge) to a [Black Knight](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Black Knight), for instance.  

Edit:  
@MindAblaze  
My point is that it never really matters that [Knight of Glory](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Knight of Glory) can't be equipped by [Mask of Riddles](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mask of Riddles). I can't attach Mask of Riddles to a pro-black creature anyway since I would need to target it. It's just not worth reminder text for the rare time where I'll cheat an equipment onto a creature without targeting.
